{"pageProps":{"article":{"title":"Polyjuice, Butterbeer and Muggles, Oh My!","category":"On the Menu","subcategory":"Recipes","publish_date":"2016-05-05T07:00:00.000Z","full_thumbnail":"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/hrp2.png?resize=355%2C230&ssl=1","mobile_thumbnail":"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/hrp2.png?resize=980%2C647&ssl=1","description":"\"...we cracked open our potion books and uncovered a few classic recipes from the wizarding world\"","content":"<div class=\"single-post-content\">\n            <div id=\"attachment_70669\" style=\"width: 778px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-70669\" data-attachment-id=\"70669\" data-permalink=\"https://dailynexus.com/2016-05-05/polyjuice-butterbeer-and-muggles-oh-my/hrp2/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/hrp2.png?fit=2448%2C3264&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"2448,3264\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta='{\"aperture\":\"0\",\"credit\":\"\",\"camera\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"created_timestamp\":\"0\",\"copyright\":\"\",\"focal_length\":\"0\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0\",\"title\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"0\"}' data-image-title=\"hrp2\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/hrp2.png?fit=188%2C250&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/hrp2.png?fit=768%2C1024&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"size-large wp-image-70669\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/hrp2-768x1024.png?resize=768%2C1024\" alt=\"Kelsey Ferrara / Daily Nexus\" width=\"768\" height=\"1024\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/hrp2.png?resize=768%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/hrp2.png?resize=188%2C250&amp;ssl=1 188w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/hrp2.png?w=1776 1776w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"><p id=\"caption-attachment-70669\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Kelsey Ferrara / Daily Nexus</em></p></div>\n<p>The Wizarding World of Harry Potter has finally made its way to California, opening its gates April 7 at Universal Studios Hollywood. This has allowed fans of all ages to explore the fantastical world of Harry Potter made famous by J.K. Rowling. In honor of this, we cracked open our potion books and uncovered a few classic recipes from the wizarding world. These recipes will put a finishing touch on any “Harry Potter” themed party and can make the magic of a movie marathon come to life.</p>\n<p><strong>Polyjuice Potion</strong><br>\nAfter sneaking into Snape’s office, we have finally discovered the secret recipe for polyjuice potion! Now you can make this mysterious brew in your very own cauldrons at home. While the original recipe took Harry and his friends a month to finish, our adaptation will only take you about 15 minutes. This recipe is for more advanced potion students, as it requires several different ingredients that may have to be stolen from Snape’s office.<br>\nThe potion is murky green in color with a texture similar to orange juice. Your polyjuice potion will have a slightly sweet and fruity taste. It also has a refreshing and fizzy flavor that reminds one of the bubbling cauldrons in the potions room.</p>\n<p><em>Ingredients</em><br>\n1/4 cup orange juice<br>\n1/4 cup Sprite<br>\n1 cup water<br>\n2 bags ginger tea<br>\n2 tsp honey<br>\n4 drops blue food coloring<br>\n2 canned peaches (sliced)</p><!--Ad Injection:random--><script type=\"text/javascript\"> \r\n\r\nfunction myAdDoneFunction(spotx_ad_found) { if(spotx_ad_found) {} else {}}; \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nfunction mobileAndTabletcheck() { \r\n\r\nvar check = false; \r\n\r\n (function(a){if(/(android|bb\\d+|meego).+mobile|avantgo|bada\\/|blackberry|blazer|compal|elaine|fennec|hiptop|iemobile|ip(hone|od)|iris|